            <h4>What is the current population of Summersville?</h4>
            <p>
                Based on the latest 2022 data from the US census, the
                current population of Summersville is 3,408.  Summersville, West Virginia is the 5,874th largest city in the US.
            </p>

            

            

            <h4>What was the peak population of Summersville?</h4>
            <p>
                
                    The peak population of Summersville was in
                    2010, when its population was
                    3,572.
                    
                        In 2010, Summersville was the
                        5,601st largest city in the US; now
                        its fallen to the 5,874th largest city in
                        the US.
                    
                    Summersville is currently
                        <span style="color: red;">
                            4.6%
                            smaller
                        </span>
                        than it was in 2010.
                    </p>
                
            </p>
            
                
                    <h4>How quickly is Summersville growing?</h4>
                
                <p>
                    
                        Summersville has grown
                        3.6% 
                        since the 2000.
                    


                    
                        Summersville, West Virginia's growth is about average.
                        55% of similarly sized
                        cities are growing faster since 2000.
                    
                </p>
            

            

            

            

    
    
        
    

    

    
   
    
